<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>1007</anchor>  <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>axt-003A</addr>  <route>axt-003A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>6</day></date> <authors><author><link href="hilary-priestley.xml" type="local">Hilary A. Priestley</link></author> </authors> <title>Alternative formulation of Zorn’s Lemma</title> <meta name="source"><tex>(ZL)''</tex> from <link href="davey-priestley-book.xml" type="local" title="Introduction to Lattices and Order">Davey and Priestley</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Every <link href="axt-003B.xml" type="local" title="Pointed dcpo">pointed dcpo</link> has a <link href="axt-0039.xml" type="local" title="Maximal element">maximal element</link>.
</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>1008</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-003B</addr>  <route>axt-003B.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>6</day></date> <authors><author><link href="hilary-priestley.xml" type="local">Hilary A. Priestley</link></author> </authors> <title>Pointed dcpo</title> <meta name="source"><b>Defn. 8.1</b> of <link href="foo" type="external">Davey and Priestley</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <b>pointed dcpo</b> is a <link href="axt-003C.xml" type="local" title="Directed-complete partial order">dcpo</link> that has a bottom element
  <tex>\bot   \in  D</tex>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>1009</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0039</addr>  <route>axt-0039.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>3</day></date> <authors><author><link href="brian-davey.xml" type="local">Brian A. Davey</link></author><author><link href="hilary-priestley.xml" type="local">Hilary A. Priestley</link></author> </authors> <title>Maximal element</title> <meta name="source"><b>Paragraph 1.23</b> of Davey and Priestley</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>P</tex> be an ordered set, and <tex>Q  \subseteq  P</tex> a subset. An element <tex>a  \in   Q</tex> is called a <b>maximal element</b> of <tex>Q</tex> if it satisfies
  <tex display="block">\forall  x  \in  X. \  a  \le  x  \rightarrow  x = a.</tex></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>1010</anchor>   <addr>davey-priestley-book</addr>  <route>davey-priestley-book.xml</route> <date><year>2002</year>  </date> <authors><author><link href="brian-davey.xml" type="local">Brian A. Davey</link></author><author><link href="hilary-priestley.xml" type="local">Hilary A. Priestley</link></author> </authors> <title>Introduction to Lattices and Order</title> <meta name="bibtex">@book{davey-priestley-book,
